The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, June 14: Godrej Beverages and Food Ltd has acquired a 100 per cent stake in Chitoor-based Nutrine Confectionery for about Rs 250 crore. Following this, Nutrine Confectionery, a household name in the south, has become a subsidiary of Godrej Beverages. Godrej Beverages is targeting a turnover of Rs 400 crore this fiscal and Rs 1,000 crore by 2008-09 by acquiring Nutrine, said Godrej group chief Adi Godrej. The group will retain the management of Nutrine.

 New Delhi, June 14: A committee set up by the boards of Air-India and Indian Airlines will meet in Mumbai on Friday and is likely to decide on the appointment of a consultant to prepare the roadmap for the merger of the two airlines. 

 New Delhi, June 14: Union minister for communications and information technology Dayanidhi Maran today unveiled a national e-governance plan covering 26 projects and eight components. It is estimated to cost Rs 23,000 crore over the next five years. 

 Mumbai, June 14: Videsh Sanchar Nigam Ltd (VSNL) will set up cyber cafes at 68 major railway stations across the country to provide travellers with Internet access.

 New Delhi, June 14: France is planning to set up aircraft manufacturing and training facilities in India.




